		b Trigonometric identities

	p
		b Symmetry
	p $$\sin (-\theta )=-\sin (\theta )$$
	p $$\cos (-\theta )=\cos (\theta )$$
	p $$\tan (-\theta )=-\tan (\theta )$$
	p
		b Expansion
	p $$\sin (\alpha +\beta )=\sin (\alpha )\cos(\beta )+\cos(\alpha )\sin (\beta )$$
	p $$\cos (\alpha +\beta )=\cos (\alpha )\cos(\beta )-\sin(\alpha )\sin (\beta )$$
	p
		b Cos and sin
	p We know
	p $$e^{i\theta }=\cos (\theta )+i\sin (\theta )$$
	p $$e^{-i\theta }=\cos (\theta )-i\sin (\theta )$$
	p So
	p $$e^{i\theta }+e^{-i\theta }=cos (\theta )+i\sin (\theta )+\cos (\theta )-i\sin (\theta )$$
	p $$\cos (\theta )=\frac{e^{i\theta }+e^{-i\theta }}{2}$$
	p And
	p $$e^{i\theta }-e^{-i\theta }=cos (\theta )+i\sin (\theta )-\cos (\theta )+i\sin (\theta )$$
	p $$\sin (\theta )=\frac{e^{i\theta }-e^{-i\theta }}{2i}$$





	p
		b  Adding waves with same frequency
	p We know that:
	p $$a\sin(bx+c)=a\sin(bx)\cos(c)+a\sin(c)\cos(bx)$$
	p So:
	p $$a\sin(bx+c)+d\sin(bx+e)=a\sin(bx)\cos(c)+a\sin(c)\cos(bx)+ d\sin(bx)\cos(e)+d\sin(e)\cos(bx)$$

	p We know that:
	p $$\sin(\theta )=\frac{e^{i\theta }-e^{-i\theta }}{2i}$$
	p So:
	p $$a\sin(bx+c)+d\sin(bx+f)=a\frac{e^{i(bx+c)}-e^{-i(bx+c)}}{2i}+d\frac{e^{i(bx+f)}-e^{-i(bx+f)}}{2i}$$
	p $$a\sin(bx+c)+d\sin(bx+f)=\frac{a(e^{i(bx+c)}-e^{-i(bx+c)})+d(e^{i(bx+f)}-e^{-i(bx+f)})}{2i}$$
	p $$a\sin(bx+c)+d\sin(bx+f)=\frac{a(e^{ibx}e^{ic}-e^{-ibx}e^{-ic})+d(e^{ibx}e^{if}-e^{-ibx}e^{-if)})}{2i}$$
	p $$a\sin(bx+c)+d\sin(bx+f)=\frac{(e^{ibx}(ae^{ic}+de^{if})-e^{-ibx}(ae^{-c}+d^{-if})}{2i}$$

